Test.Name: Correct response with one token
Test.Description: There is only one DoorInfo on the DUT This DoorInfo has requared cabalities DUT sends correct response on PullMessages requests Set Operation delay to 30 s Set InitialTerminationTime to 60s Check that TT will send PullMessages during Operation delay

Test.Name: Correct response with more than one token (select last)
Test.Description: Select tokenDoorPoint3 from the list.

Test.Name: Correct response with more than one token (select first)
Test.Description: Select tokenDoorPoint1 from the list.

Test.Name: Changed property event during waiting of Initilized
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends event with Changed property operation for not tested door token in the first PM DUT sends expected event in the second PM

Test.Name: Check a litle Operation delay
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 15 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends all events at once after request Check that there is not following PM after PM response with no event

Test.Name: More than one Initilized events
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends 2 Initilized events in the first PullMessage response TT can not fail test

Test.Name: More than one Changed events
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends 2 Changed events in the one PullMessage response TT can not fail test

Test.Name: Several Initialized events
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends not required Initialized event at the same times DUT seds required Initialized event last

Test.Name: Several Initialized events (no required token)
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Incorrect response: DUT sends not required Initialized event at the same times DUT doen't send required Initialized event

Test.Name: Several Changed events
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends several Changed events for tested DoorToken State value of the last event is Loked

Test.Name: Several Changed events (last event is not Locked)
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Incorrect response: DUT sends several Changed events for tested DoorToken State value of the last event is not Loked

Test.Name: Renew is reqiured during waiting of Initialized events (several PM)
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 30 s Set Operation Delay to 60 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends not required Initialized event at the same times DUT seds required Initialized event last Renew is required

Test.Name: Renew is reqiured during waiting of Initialized events (one PM)
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 30 s Set Operation Delay to 60 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends required Initialized event in 55 s Renew is required during waiting of response

Test.Name: Renew is reqiured during waiting of Changed events (several PM)
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 30 s Set Operation Delay to 60 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends several Changed events for tested DoorToken State value of the last event is Loked Renew is required when PM is setting during operation delay (catch Changed event)

Test.Name: Renew is reqiured during waiting of Changed events (one PM)
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 30 s Set Operation Delay to 60 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends one Changed events for tested DoorToken in 60s State value of the event is Loked Renew is required when PM is setting during operation delay (catch Changed event)

Test.Name: Initilaized event was sent with delay
Test.Description: Set Subscribtion timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends one correct Initialized events for tested DoorToken in 55s

Test.Name: Changed event was sent with delay
Test.Description: Set Subscribtion timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 30 s Select the first door for test Correct response: DUT sends one correct Changed events for tested DoorToken in 55s

Test.Name: There is Initialized events during waiting for Changed events (correct case)
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 60 s Select the first door for test Incorrect response: DUT sends Initialized event for not tested doors during waiting for Changed event Last event is correct

Test.Name: There is Initialized events during waiting for Changed events (incorrect case)
Test.Description: Set Subscription timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 60 s Select the first door for test Incorrect response: DUT sends Initialized event tested door during waiting for Changed event Last event is correct

Test.Name: Renew beetwin operations
Test.Description: Set Subscribtion timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 300 s Select the first door for test Correct response with Renew beetwin operations

Test.Name: Corect response: UnacceptableTerminationTimeFault on Renew
Test.Description: Set Subscribtion timeout to 60 s Set Operation Delay to 300 s Select the first door for test Correct response with Renew beetwin operations DUT sends UnacceptableTerminationTimeFault on Renew with included acceptable values for InitialTerminationTime

Test.Name: Fault on PullMessages (TerminationTime)
Test.Description: Set Operation delay to 30 s Set InitialTerminationTime to 60s DUT does not accept Termination Time on PullMessages requests and sends fault TT can fail tests (because there is requriment that DUT shall accept the such Termination Time) Or the DUT can re-send PM with new Termination Time (Check that Termination Time in request is correct)

Test.Name: Fault on PullMessages
Test.Description: DUT sends fault on PullMessage (NotImplemented)

Test.Name: No response on PullMessages
Test.Description: DUT sends no response on PullMessage

Test.Name: Fault on Unsubscribe
Test.Description: Set Operation delay to 30 s Set InitialTerminationTime to 60s DUT sends fault on Unsubscribe. Check that DUT will delete subscription. Test shall be passed.

Test.Name: No response on Unsubscribe
Test.Description: Set Operation delay to 30 s Set InitialTerminationTime to 60s DUT sends no response on Unsubscribe. Check that DUT will delete subscription. Test shall be passed.

Test.Name: No wsnt:Message in notification message
Test.Description: DUT returns GetAccessPointInfoList with one token Notification message contains no wsnt:Message elements - NotificationMessage does not correspond to schema

Test.Name: Correct response: incorrect type of Data.SimpleItem.Name for not tested Door (Initialized event)
Test.Description: Set Operation delay to 30 s Set InitialTerminationTime to 60s DUT sends Initialized event for not tested door with incorrect value of Data.SimpleItem.Name

Test.Name: Incorrect response: incorrect type of Data.SimpleItem.Name for not last event (Changed event)
Test.Description: Set Operation delay to 30 s Set InitialTerminationTime to 60s DUT sends not last Changed event for tested door with incorrect value of Data.SimpleItem.Name

Test.Name: Incorrect response: incorrect type of Data.SimpleItem.Name for tested Door (Initialized event)
Test.Description: Set Operation delay to 30 s Set InitialTerminationTime to 60s DUT sends Initialized event for tested door with incorrect value of Data.SimpleItem.Name

Test.Name: Incorrect response: incorrect type of Data.SimpleItem.Name for the last event (Changed event)
Test.Description: Set Operation delay to 30 s Set InitialTerminationTime to 60s DUT sends the last Changed event for tested door with incorrect value of Data.SimpleItem.Name

Test.Description: DUT does not accept Timeout in CPPS request

Test.Description: DUT sends fault on CPPS (NotImplemented)
